{"id":642,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":642,"title":"Hymns","subtitle":"","short_title":"Hymns","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hymns","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hymns.t1","order":".000.1652"},[".title","Hymns"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hymns.p1","order":".000.1653"},"There are various references in the New Testament to the use of hymns, such as in the account of the Last Supper (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/26.30"},"Matt. 26:30"],"), where the hymn would be part of the Hallel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/113?span=113-118"},"Ps. 113–18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/4.24"},"Acts 4:24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/16.25"},"16:25"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/14.15,26"},"1 Cor. 14:15, 26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/eph/5.19"},"Eph. 5:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/col/3.16"},"Col. 3:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/5.13"},"James 5:13"],"). Psalmody and hymnody were highly developed in the religious services of the Jews and were thus easily continued in Christian worship. The Gospel hymns, such as the",["span.translit","Magnificat"],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.46-55"},"Luke 1:46–55"],"), the",["span.translit","Benedictus"],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.68-79"},"1:68–79"],"), the",["span.translit","Gloria in Excelsis"],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.14"},"2:14"],"), and the",["span.translit","Nunc Dimittis"],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.29-32"},"2:29–32"],"), have from early times been used in public worship."]]],"refs":null}
